53/**
54 * Generic iterator which can operate on types that expose the following:
55 * - A type called ElementType representing the contained type.
56 * - A method SizeType Num() const that returns the number of items in the container.
57 * - A method bool IsValidIndex(SizeType index) which returns whether a given index is valid in the container.
58 * - A method T& operator\[\](SizeType index) which returns a reference to a contained object by index.
59 * - A method void RemoveAt(SizeType index) which removes the element at index
60 */
61template <typename ContainerType, typename ElementType, typename SizeType>
62class TIndexedContainerIterator
63{
64public:
65 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] TIndexedContainerIterator(ContainerType& InContainer, SizeType StartIndex = 0)
66 : Container(InContainer)
67 , Index (StartIndex)
68 {
69 }
70
71 /** Advances iterator to the next element in the container. */
72 UE_NODEBUG TIndexedContainerIterator& operator++()
73 {
74 ++Index;
75 return *this;
76 }
77 UE_NODEBUG TIndexedContainerIterator operator++(int)
78 {
79 TIndexedContainerIterator Tmp(*this);
80 ++Index;
81 return Tmp;
82 }
83
84 /** Moves iterator to the previous element in the container. */
85 UE_NODEBUG TIndexedContainerIterator& operator--()
86 {
87 --Index;
88 return *this;
89 }
90 UE_NODEBUG TIndexedContainerIterator operator--(int)
91 {
92 TIndexedContainerIterator Tmp(*this);
93 --Index;
94 return Tmp;
95 }
96
97 /** iterator arithmetic support */
98 UE_NODEBUG TIndexedContainerIterator& operator+=(SizeType Offset)
99 {
100 Index += Offset;
101 return *this;
102 }
103
104 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] TIndexedContainerIterator operator+(SizeType Offset) const
105 {
106 TIndexedContainerIterator Tmp(*this);
107 return Tmp += Offset;
108 }
109
110 UE_NODEBUG TIndexedContainerIterator& operator-=(SizeType Offset)
111 {
112 return *this += -Offset;
113 }
114
115 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] TIndexedContainerIterator operator-(SizeType Offset) const
116 {
117 TIndexedContainerIterator Tmp(*this);
118 return Tmp -= Offset;
119 }
120
121 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE ElementType& operator* () const
122 {
123 return Container[ Index ];
124 }
125
126 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE ElementType* operator->() const
127 {
128 return &Container[ Index ];
129 }
130
131 /** conversion to "bool" returning true if the iterator has not reached the last element. */
132 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE explicit operator bool() const
133 {
134 return Container.IsValidIndex(Index);
135 }
136
137 /** Returns an index to the current element. */
138 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] SizeType GetIndex() const
139 {
140 return Index;
141 }
142
143 /** Resets the iterator to the first element. */
144 UE_NODEBUG void Reset()
145 {
146 Index = 0;
147 }
148
149 /** Sets the iterator to one past the last element. */
150 UE_NODEBUG void SetToEnd()
151 {
152 Index = Container.Num();
153 }
154
155 /** Removes current element in array. This invalidates the current iterator value and it must be incremented */
156 UE_NODEBUG void RemoveCurrent()
157 {
158 Container.RemoveAt(Index);
159 Index--;
160 }
161
162 /**
163 * Removes current element in array by swapping it with the end element and popping it from the end.
164 * This invalidates the current iterator value and it must be incremented.
165 * Note this modifies the order of the remaining elements in the array.
166 */
167 UE_NODEBUG void RemoveCurrentSwap()
168 {
169 Container.RemoveAtSwap(Index);
170 Index--;
171 }
172
173 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE bool operator==(const TIndexedContainerIterator& Rhs) const
174 {
175 return &Container == &Rhs.Container && Index == Rhs.Index;
176 }
177#if !PLATFORM_COMPILER_HAS_GENERATED_COMPARISON_OPERATORS
178 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE bool operator!=(const TIndexedContainerIterator& Rhs) const
179 {
180 return &Container != &Rhs.Container || Index != Rhs.Index;
181 }
182#endif
183
184private:
185 ContainerType& Container;
186 SizeType Index;
187};
188

198#if TARRAY_RANGED_FOR_CHECKS
199 /**
200 * Pointer-like iterator type for ranged-for loops which checks that the
201 * container hasn't been resized during iteration.
202 */
203 template <typename ElementType, typename SizeType, bool bReverse = false>
204 struct TCheckedPointerIterator
205 {
206 // This iterator type only supports the minimal functionality needed to support
207 // C++ ranged-for syntax. For example, it does not provide post-increment ++ nor ==.
208 //
209 // We do add an operator-- to help FString implementation
210
211 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] explicit TCheckedPointerIterator(const SizeType& InNum, ElementType* InPtr)
212 : Ptr (InPtr)
213 , CurrentNum(InNum)
214 , InitialNum(InNum)
215 {
216 }
217
218 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE ElementType& operator*() const
219 {
220 if constexpr (bReverse)
221 {
222 return *(Ptr - 1);
223 }
224 else
225 {
226 return *Ptr;
227 }
228 }
229
230 UE_NODEBUG FORCEINLINE TCheckedPointerIterator& operator++()
231 {
232 if constexpr (bReverse)
233 {
234 --Ptr;
235 }
236 else
237 {
238 ++Ptr;
239 }
240 return *this;
241 }
242
243 UE_NODEBUG FORCEINLINE TCheckedPointerIterator& operator--()
244 {
245 if constexpr (bReverse)
246 {
247 ++Ptr;
248 }
249 else
250 {
251 --Ptr;
252 }
253 return *this;
254 }
255
256 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE bool operator!=(const TCheckedPointerIterator& Rhs) const
257 {
258 // We only need to do the check in this operator, because no other operator will be
259 // called until after this one returns.
260 //
261 // Also, we should only need to check one side of this comparison - if the other iterator isn't
262 // even from the same array then the compiler has generated bad code.
263 ensureMsgf(CurrentNum == InitialNum, TEXT("Array has changed during ranged-for iteration!"));
264 return Ptr != Rhs.Ptr;
265 }
266
267 private:
268 ElementType* Ptr;
269 const SizeType& CurrentNum;
270 SizeType InitialNum;
271 };
272#endif

313 template <typename FromArrayType, typename ToArrayType>
314 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] constexpr bool CanMoveTArrayPointersBetweenArrayTypes()
315 {
316 using FromAllocatorType = typename FromArrayType::AllocatorType;
317 using ToAllocatorType = typename ToArrayType::AllocatorType;
318 using FromElementType = typename FromArrayType::ElementType;
319 using ToElementType = typename ToArrayType::ElementType;
320 using UnqualifiedFromElementType = std::remove_cv_t<FromElementType>;
321 using UnqualifiedToElementType = std::remove_cv_t<ToElementType>;
322
323 // Allocators must be equal or move-compatible...
324 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<FromAllocatorType, ToAllocatorType> || TCanMoveBetweenAllocators<FromAllocatorType, ToAllocatorType>::Value)
325 {
326 return
327 !TLosesQualifiersFromTo_V<FromElementType, ToElementType> &&
328 (
329 std::is_same_v <const ToElementType, const FromElementType> || // The element type of the container must be the same, or...
330 TIsBitwiseConstructible<UnqualifiedToElementType, UnqualifiedFromElementType>::Value // ... the element type of the source container must be bitwise constructible from the element type in the destination container
331 );
332 }
333 else
334 {
335 return false;
336 }
337 }
338
339 // Assume elements are compatible with themselves - avoids problems with generated copy
340 // constructors of arrays of forwarded types, e.g.:
341 //
342 // struct FThing;
343 //
344 // struct FOuter
345 // {
346 // TArray<FThing> Arr; // this will cause errors without this workaround
347 // };
348 template <typename DestType, typename SourceType>
349 constexpr bool TArrayElementsAreCompatible_V = std::disjunction_v<std::is_same<DestType, std::decay_t<SourceType>>, std::is_constructible<DestType, SourceType>>;

358 [[noreturn]] CORE_API void OnInvalidArrayNum(unsigned long long NewNum);

360 // A hacky way to get the SizeType, since it's defined in the
361 // (outer) allocator type, not the (inner) allocator instance type
362 template <typename AllocatorInstanceType>
363 using TAllocatorSizeType_T = decltype(std::declval<AllocatorInstanceType&>().GetInitialCapacity());
364
365 // Flags are passed as a uint32 to minimize PDB impact of these generated symbols.
366 //
367 // 1 == TAllocatorTraits<>::SupportsElementAlignment
368 // 2 == TAllocatorTraits<>::SupportsSlackTracking
369 //
370 // When C++20 is guaranteed, concept checks can be used instead.
371 template <typename AllocatorType>
372 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] constexpr uint32 GetAllocatorFlags()
373 {
374 uint32 Result = 0;
375 if constexpr (TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsElementAlignment)
376 {
377 Result |= 1;
378 }
379 if constexpr (TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsSlackTracking)
380 {
381 Result |= 2;
382 }
383 return Result;
384 }

387 // Called only when we KNOW we are going to do a realloc increasing by 1.
388 // In this case, we know that max == num and can simplify things in a very
389 // hot location in the code.
390 // This returns the old ArrayMax in order to save a register clobber/reload.
391 template <uint32 Flags, typename AllocatorInstanceType>
392 FORCEINLINE TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc_Impl(
393 uint32 ElementSize,
394 uint32 ElementAlignment,
395 AllocatorInstanceType& AllocatorInstance,
396 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>& ArrayMax
397 )
398 {
399 using SizeType = TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>;
400 using USizeType = std::make_unsigned_t<SizeType>;
401
402 const USizeType UOldMax = (USizeType)ArrayMax;
403 const USizeType UNewNum = UOldMax + 1U;
404 const SizeType OldMax = (SizeType)UOldMax;
405 const SizeType NewNum = (SizeType)UNewNum;
406
407 // This should only happen when we've underflowed or overflowed SizeType
408 if (NewNum < OldMax)
409 {
410 OnInvalidArrayNum((unsigned long long)UNewNum);
411 }
412
413 SizeType NewMax;
414 if constexpr (!!(Flags & 1)) // TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsElementAlignment
415 {
416 NewMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackGrow(NewNum, OldMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
417 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(UOldMax, NewMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
418 }
419 else
420 {
421 NewMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackGrow(NewNum, OldMax, ElementSize);
422 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(UOldMax, NewMax, ElementSize);
423 }
424 ArrayMax = NewMax;
425 #if UE_ENABLE_ARRAY_SLACK_TRACKING
426 if constexpr (!!(Flags & 2)) // TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsSlackTracking
427 {
428 AllocatorInstance.SlackTrackerLogNum(NewNum);
429 }
430 #endif
431
432 return OldMax;
433 }
434
435 // Version for small sizes/alignments. This allows the parameter setup to be a single instruction
436 // note the uint16 limitation allows for a single instruction setup on arm.
437 template <uint32 Flags, typename AllocatorInstanceType>
438 FORCENOINLINE TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc_Tiny(
439 uint16 ElementSizeAndAlignment,
440 AllocatorInstanceType& AllocatorInstance,
441 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>& ArrayMax
442 )
443 {
444 return ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc_Impl<Flags, AllocatorInstanceType>(ElementSizeAndAlignment & 0xff, ElementSizeAndAlignment >> 8, AllocatorInstance, ArrayMax);
445 }

447 template <uint32 Flags, typename AllocatorInstanceType>
448 FORCENOINLINE TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc(
449 uint32 ElementSize,
450 uint32 ElementAlignment,
451 AllocatorInstanceType& AllocatorInstance,
452 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>& ArrayMax
453 )
454 {
455 return ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc_Impl<Flags, AllocatorInstanceType>(ElementSize, ElementAlignment, AllocatorInstance, ArrayMax);
456 }

458 // This should be used for repeated growing operations when reallocations are to be amortized over multiple inserts.
459 template <uint32 Flags, typename AllocatorInstanceType>
460 FORCENOINLINE TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> ReallocGrow(
461 uint32 ElementSize,
462 uint32 ElementAlignment,
463 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> Count,
464 AllocatorInstanceType& AllocatorInstance,
465 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>& ArrayNum,
466 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>& ArrayMax
467 )
468 {
469 using SizeType = TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>;
470 using USizeType = std::make_unsigned_t<SizeType>;
471
472 const USizeType UCount = (USizeType)Count;
473 const USizeType UOldNum = (USizeType)ArrayNum;
474 const USizeType UOldMax = (USizeType)ArrayMax;
475 const USizeType UNewNum = UOldNum + UCount;
476 const SizeType OldNum = (SizeType)UOldNum;
477 const SizeType OldMax = (SizeType)UOldMax;
478 const SizeType NewNum = (SizeType)UNewNum;
479
480 checkSlow((OldNum >= 0) & (OldMax >= OldNum) & (Count >= 0)); // & for one branch
481
482 ArrayNum = NewNum;
483
484#if DO_GUARD_SLOW
485 if (UNewNum > UOldMax)
486#else
487 // SECURITY - This check will guard against negative counts too, in case the checkSlow above is compiled out.
488 // However, it results in slightly worse code generation.
489 if (UCount > UOldMax - UOldNum)
490#endif
491 {
492 // This should only happen when we've underflowed or overflowed SizeType
493 if (NewNum < OldNum)
494 {
495 OnInvalidArrayNum((unsigned long long)UNewNum);
496 }
497 SizeType NewMax;
498 if constexpr (!!(Flags & 1)) // TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsElementAlignment
499 {
500 NewMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackGrow(NewNum, OldMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
501 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(UOldNum, NewMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
502 }
503 else
504 {
505 NewMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackGrow(NewNum, OldMax, ElementSize);
506 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(UOldNum, NewMax, ElementSize);
507 }
508 ArrayMax = NewMax;
509#if UE_ENABLE_ARRAY_SLACK_TRACKING
510 if constexpr (!!(Flags & 2)) // TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsSlackTracking
511 {
512 AllocatorInstance.SlackTrackerLogNum(NewNum);
513 }
514#endif
515 }
516
517 return OldNum;
518 }

520 // This should be used for repeated shrinking operations when reallocations are to be amortized over multiple removals.
521 template <uint32 Flags, typename AllocatorInstanceType>
522 FORCENOINLINE void ReallocShrink(
523 uint32 ElementSize,
524 uint32 ElementAlignment,
525 AllocatorInstanceType& AllocatorInstance,
526 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> ArrayNum,
527 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>& ArrayMax
528 )
529 {
530 using SizeType = TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>;
531
532 SizeType OldArrayMax = ArrayMax;
533
534 if constexpr (!!(Flags & 1)) // TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsElementAlignment
535 {
536 SizeType NewArrayMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackShrink(ArrayNum, OldArrayMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
537 if (NewArrayMax != OldArrayMax)
538 {
539 ArrayMax = NewArrayMax;
540 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(ArrayNum, NewArrayMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
541 }
542 }
543 else
544 {
545 SizeType NewArrayMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackShrink(ArrayNum, OldArrayMax, ElementSize);
546 if (NewArrayMax != OldArrayMax)
547 {
548 ArrayMax = NewArrayMax;
549 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(ArrayNum, NewArrayMax, ElementSize);
550 }
551 }
552 }

554 // This should be used for setting an allocation to a specific size.
555 // Precondition: NewMax >= ArrayNum.
556 template <uint32 Flags, typename AllocatorInstanceType>
557 FORCENOINLINE void ReallocTo(
558 uint32 ElementSize,
559 uint32 ElementAlignment,
560 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> NewMax,
561 AllocatorInstanceType& AllocatorInstance,
562 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> ArrayNum,
563 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>& ArrayMax
564 )
565 {
566 if constexpr (!!(Flags & 1)) // TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsElementAlignment
567 {
568 if (NewMax)
569 {
570 NewMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackReserve(NewMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
571 }
572 if (NewMax != ArrayMax)
573 {
574 ArrayMax = NewMax;
575 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(ArrayNum, NewMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
576 }
577 }
578 else
579 {
580 if (NewMax)
581 {
582 NewMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackReserve(NewMax, ElementSize);
583 }
584 if (NewMax != ArrayMax)
585 {
586 ArrayMax = NewMax;
587 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(ArrayNum, NewMax, ElementSize);
588 }
589 }
590 }

592 template <uint32 Flags, typename AllocatorInstanceType>
593 FORCENOINLINE void ReallocForCopy(
594 uint32 ElementSize,
595 uint32 ElementAlignment,
596 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> NewMax,
597 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> PrevMax,
598 AllocatorInstanceType& AllocatorInstance,
599 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType> ArrayNum,
600 TAllocatorSizeType_T<AllocatorInstanceType>& ArrayMax
601 )
602 {
603 if constexpr (!!(Flags & 1)) // TAllocatorTraits<AllocatorType>::SupportsElementAlignment
604 {
605 if (NewMax)
606 {
607 NewMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackReserve(NewMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
608 }
609 if (NewMax > PrevMax)
610 {
611 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(0, NewMax, ElementSize, ElementAlignment);
612 }
613 else
614 {
615 NewMax = PrevMax;
616 }
617 }
618 else
619 {
620 if (NewMax)
621 {
622 NewMax = AllocatorInstance.CalculateSlackReserve(NewMax, ElementSize);
623 }
624 if (NewMax > PrevMax)
625 {
626 AllocatorInstance.ResizeAllocation(0, NewMax, ElementSize);
627 }
628 else
629 {
630 NewMax = PrevMax;
631 }
632 }
633 ArrayMax = NewMax;
634 }

639/**
640 * Templated dynamic array
641 *
642 * A dynamically sized array of typed elements. Makes the assumption that your elements are relocate-able;
643 * i.e. that they can be transparently moved to new memory without a copy constructor. The main implication
644 * is that pointers to elements in the TArray may be invalidated by adding or removing other elements to the array.
645 * Removal of elements is O(N) and invalidates the indices of subsequent elements.
646 *
647 * Caution: as noted below some methods are not safe for element types that require constructors.
648 *
649 **/
650template<typename InElementType, typename InAllocatorType>
651class TArray
652{
653 template <typename OtherInElementType, typename OtherAllocator>
654 friend class TArray;
655
656public:
657 using SizeType = typename InAllocatorType::SizeType ;
658 using ElementType = InElementType;
659 using AllocatorType = InAllocatorType;
660
661private:
662 using USizeType = typename std::make_unsigned_t<SizeType>;
663
664public:
665 using ElementAllocatorType = std::conditional_t<
666 AllocatorType::NeedsElementType,
667 typename AllocatorType::template ForElementType<ElementType>,
668 typename AllocatorType::ForAnyElementType
669 >;
670
671 static_assert(std::is_signed_v<SizeType>, "TArray only supports signed index types");
672
673 /**
674 * Constructor, initializes element number counters.
675 */
676 [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE TArray()
677 : ArrayNum(0)
678 , ArrayMax(AllocatorInstance.GetInitialCapacity())
679 {
680 }
681
682 /**
683 * Constructor from a raw array of elements.
684 *
685 * @param Ptr A pointer to an array of elements to copy.
686 * @param Count The number of elements to copy from Ptr.
687 * @see Append
688 */
689 [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE TArray(const ElementType* Ptr, SizeType Count)
690 {
691 if (Count < 0)
692 {
693 // Cast to USizeType first to prevent sign extension on negative sizes, producing unusually large values.
694 UE::Core::Private::OnInvalidArrayNum((unsigned long long)(USizeType)Count);
695 }
696
697 check(Ptr != nullptr || Count == 0);
698
699 CopyToEmpty(Ptr, Count, 0);
700 }
701
702 template <typename OtherElementType, typename OtherSizeType>
703 [[nodiscard]] explicit TArray(const TArrayView<OtherElementType, OtherSizeType>& Other);
704
705 /**
706 * Initializer list constructor
707 */
708 [[nodiscard]] TArray(std::initializer_list<InElementType> InitList)
709 {
710 // This is not strictly legal, as std::initializer_list's iterators are not guaranteed to be pointers, but
711 // this appears to be the case on all of our implementations. Also, if it's not true on a new implementation,
712 // it will fail to compile rather than behave badly.
713 CopyToEmpty(InitList.begin(), (SizeType)InitList.size(), 0);
714 }
715
716 /**
717 * Copy constructor with changed allocator. Use the common routine to perform the copy.
718 *
719 * @param Other The source array to copy.
720 */
721 template <
722 typename OtherElementType,
723 typename OtherAllocator
724 UE_REQUIRES(UE::Core::Private::TArrayElementsAreCompatible_V<ElementType, const OtherElementType&>)
725 >
726 [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE explicit TArray(const TArray<OtherElementType, OtherAllocator>& Other)
727 {
728 CopyToEmpty(Other.GetData(), Other.Num(), 0);
729 }
730
731 /**
732 * Copy constructor. Use the common routine to perform the copy.
733 *
734 * @param Other The source array to copy.
735 */
736 [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE TArray(const TArray& Other)
737 {
738 CopyToEmpty(Other.GetData(), Other.Num(), 0);
739 }
740
741 /**
742 * Copy constructor. Use the common routine to perform the copy.
743 *
744 * @param Other The source array to copy.
745 * @param ExtraSlack Tells how much extra memory should be preallocated
746 * at the end of the array in the number of elements.
747 */
748 [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE TArray(const TArray& Other, SizeType ExtraSlack)
749 {
750 CopyToEmptyWithSlack(Other.GetData(), Other.Num(), 0, ExtraSlack);
751 }
752
753 /**
754 * Initializer list assignment operator. First deletes all currently contained elements
755 * and then copies from initializer list.
756 *
757 * @param InitList The initializer_list to copy from.
758 */
759 TArray& operator=(std::initializer_list<InElementType> InitList)
760 {
761 DestructItems(GetData(), ArrayNum);
762 // This is not strictly legal, as std::initializer_list's iterators are not guaranteed to be pointers, but
763 // this appears to be the case on all of our implementations. Also, if it's not true on a new implementation,
764 // it will fail to compile rather than behave badly.
765 CopyToEmpty(InitList.begin(), (SizeType)InitList.size(), ArrayMax);
766 return *this;
767 }
768
769 /**
770 * Assignment operator. First deletes all currently contained elements
771 * and then copies from other array.
772 *
773 * AllocatorType changing version.
774 *
775 * @param Other The source array to assign from.
776 */
777 template<typename OtherAllocatorType>
778 TArray& operator=(const TArray<ElementType, OtherAllocatorType>& Other)
779 {
780 DestructItems(GetData(), ArrayNum);
781 CopyToEmpty(Other.GetData(), Other.Num(), ArrayMax);
782 return *this;
783 }
784
785 /**
786 * Assignment operator. First deletes all currently contained elements
787 * and then copies from other array.
788 *
789 * @param Other The source array to assign from.
790 */
791 TArray& operator=(const TArray& Other)
792 {
793 if (this != &Other)
794 {
795 DestructItems(GetData(), ArrayNum);
796 CopyToEmpty(Other.GetData(), Other.Num(), ArrayMax);
797 }
798 return *this;
799 }

802 TArray& operator=(const TArrayView<OtherElementType, OtherSizeType>& Other);

806 FORCEINLINE void SlackTrackerNumChanged()
807 {
808#if UE_ENABLE_ARRAY_SLACK_TRACKING
809 if constexpr (TAllocatorTraits<InAllocatorType>::SupportsSlackTracking)
810 {
811 AllocatorInstance.SlackTrackerLogNum(ArrayNum);
812 }
813#endif
814 }

816 /**
817 * Moves or copies array. Depends on the array type traits.
818 *
819 * @param ToArray Array to move into.
820 * @param FromArray Array to move from.
821 * @param PrevMax The previous allocated size.
822 */
823 template <typename FromArrayType, typename ToArrayType>
824 static FORCEINLINE void MoveOrCopy(ToArrayType& ToArray, FromArrayType& FromArray, SizeType PrevMax)
825 {
826 if constexpr (UE::Core::Private::CanMoveTArrayPointersBetweenArrayTypes<FromArrayType, ToArrayType>())
827 {
828 // Move
829
830 static_assert(std::is_same_v<TArray, ToArrayType>, "MoveOrCopy is expected to be called with the current array type as the destination");
831
832 using FromAllocatorType = typename FromArrayType::AllocatorType;
833 using ToAllocatorType = typename ToArrayType::AllocatorType;
834
835 if constexpr (TCanMoveBetweenAllocators<FromAllocatorType, ToAllocatorType>::Value)
836 {
837 ToArray.AllocatorInstance.template MoveToEmptyFromOtherAllocator<FromAllocatorType>(FromArray.AllocatorInstance);
838 }
839 else
840 {
841 ToArray.AllocatorInstance.MoveToEmpty(FromArray.AllocatorInstance);
842 }
843
844 ToArray .ArrayNum = (SizeType)FromArray.ArrayNum;
845 ToArray .ArrayMax = (SizeType)FromArray.ArrayMax;
846
847 // Ensure the destination container could hold the source range (when the allocator size types shrink)
848 if constexpr (sizeof(USizeType) < sizeof(typename FromArrayType::USizeType))
849 {
850 if (ToArray.ArrayNum != FromArray.ArrayNum || ToArray.ArrayMax != FromArray.ArrayMax)
851 {
852 // Cast to USizeType first to prevent sign extension on negative sizes, producing unusually large values.
853 UE::Core::Private::OnInvalidArrayNum((unsigned long long)(USizeType)ToArray.ArrayNum);
854 }
855 }
856
857 FromArray.ArrayNum = 0;
858 FromArray.ArrayMax = FromArray.AllocatorInstance.GetInitialCapacity();
859
860 FromArray.SlackTrackerNumChanged();
861 ToArray.SlackTrackerNumChanged();
862 }
863 else
864 {
865 // Copy
866
867 ToArray.CopyToEmpty(FromArray.GetData(), FromArray.Num(), PrevMax);
868 }
869 }
870
871 /**
872 * Moves or copies array. Depends on the array type traits.
873 *
874 * @param ToArray Array to move into.
875 * @param FromArray Array to move from.
876 * @param PrevMax The previous allocated size.
877 * @param ExtraSlack Tells how much extra memory should be preallocated
878 * at the end of the array in the number of elements.
879 */
880 template <typename FromArrayType, typename ToArrayType>
881 static FORCEINLINE void MoveOrCopyWithSlack(ToArrayType& ToArray, FromArrayType& FromArray, SizeType PrevMax, SizeType ExtraSlack)
882 {
883 if constexpr (UE::Core::Private::CanMoveTArrayPointersBetweenArrayTypes<FromArrayType, ToArrayType>())
884 {
885 // Move
886
887 MoveOrCopy(ToArray, FromArray, PrevMax);
888
889 USizeType LocalArrayNum = (USizeType)ToArray.ArrayNum;
890 USizeType NewMax = (USizeType)LocalArrayNum + (USizeType)ExtraSlack;
891
892 // This should only happen when we've underflowed or overflowed SizeType
893 if ((SizeType)NewMax < (SizeType)LocalArrayNum)
894 {
895 UE::Core::Private::OnInvalidArrayNum((unsigned long long)ExtraSlack);
896 }
897
898 ToArray.Reserve(NewMax);
899 }
900 else
901 {
902 // Copy
903
904 ToArray.CopyToEmptyWithSlack(FromArray.GetData(), FromArray.Num(), PrevMax, ExtraSlack);
905 }
906 }

1058 * @param Index Index to check.

1063
1064 // Template property, branch will be optimized out
1065 if constexpr (AllocatorType::RequireRangeCheck)
1066 {
1067 checkf((Index >= 0) & (Index < ArrayNum),TEXT("Array index out of bounds: %lld into an array of size %lld"),(long long)Index, (long long)ArrayNum); // & for one branch
1068 }

1075 * @param Count Number of elements in the range.

1078 {
1079 CheckInvariants();
1080
1081 // Template property, branch will be optimized out
1082 if constexpr (AllocatorType::RequireRangeCheck)
1083 {
1084 checkf((Count >= 0) & (Index >= 0) & (Index + Count <= ArrayNum), TEXT("Array range out of bounds: index %lld and length %lld into an array of size %lld"), (long long)Index, (long long)Count, (long long)ArrayNum); // & for one branch
1085 }

1162 /**
1163 * Pops element from the array.
1164 *
1165 * @param AllowShrinking If this call allows shrinking of the array during element remove.
1166 * @returns Popped element.
1167 */
1168 ElementType Pop(EAllowShrinking AllowShrinking = EAllowShrinking::Default)
1169 {
1170 RangeCheck(0);
1171 ElementType Result = MoveTempIfPossible(GetData()[ArrayNum - 1]);
1172 RemoveAtImpl(ArrayNum - 1);
1173 if (AllowShrinking == EAllowShrinking::Yes)
1174 {
1175 UE::Core::Private::ReallocShrink<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(
1176 sizeof(ElementType),
1177 alignof(ElementType),
1178 AllocatorInstance,
1179 ArrayNum,
1180 ArrayMax
1181 );
1182 }
1183 return Result;
1184 }

1187 {
1188 return Pop(bAllowShrinking ? EAllowShrinking::Yes : EAllowShrinking::No);

1264 /**

1266 *
1267 * @see Slack
1268 */

1270 {

1272 if (ArrayMax != ArrayNum)
1273 {
1274 UE::Core::Private::ReallocTo<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(
1275 sizeof(ElementType),
1276 alignof(ElementType),
1277 ArrayNum,
1278 AllocatorInstance,
1279 ArrayNum,
1280 ArrayMax
1281 );
1282 }

1285 /**
1286 * Finds element within the array.

1299 /**
1300 * Finds element within the array.
1301 *
1302 * @param Item Item to look for.
1303 * @returns Index of the found element. INDEX_NONE otherwise.
1304 * @see FindLast, FindLastByPredicate
1305 */
1306 [[nodiscard]] SizeType Find(const ElementType& Item) const
1307 {
1308 const ElementType* RESTRICT Start = GetData();
1309 for (const ElementType* RESTRICT Data = Start, *RESTRICT DataEnd = Data + ArrayNum; Data != DataEnd; ++Data)
1310 {
1311 if (*Data == Item)
1312 {
1313 return static_cast<SizeType>(Data - Start);
1314 }
1315 }
1316 return INDEX_NONE;
1317 }

1321 *
1322 * @param Item Item to look for.

1324 * @returns True if found. False otherwise.
1325 * @see Find, FindLastByPredicate
1326 */
1327 UE_NODEBUG FORCEINLINE bool FindLast(const ElementType& Item, SizeType& Index) const
1328 {
1329 Index = this->FindLast(Item);
1330 return Index != INDEX_NONE;

1334 * Finds element within the array starting from the end.
1335 *
1336 * @param Item Item to look for.
1337 * @returns Index of the found element. INDEX_NONE otherwise.
1338 */
1339 [[nodiscard]] SizeType FindLast(const ElementType& Item) const
1340 {
1341 for (const ElementType* RESTRICT Start = GetData(), *RESTRICT Data = Start + ArrayNum; Data != Start; )
1342 {
1343 --Data;
1344 if (*Data == Item)
1345 {
1346 return static_cast<SizeType>(Data - Start);
1347 }
1348 }
1349 return INDEX_NONE;

1352 /**
1353 * Searches an initial subrange of the array for the last occurrence of an element which matches the specified predicate.
1354 *
1355 * @param Pred Predicate taking array element and returns true if element matches search criteria, false otherwise.
1356 * @param Count The number of elements from the front of the array through which to search.
1357 * @returns Index of the found element. INDEX_NONE otherwise.
1358 */
1359 template <typename Predicate>
1360 [[nodiscard]] SizeType FindLastByPredicate(Predicate Pred, SizeType Count) const
1361 {
1362 check(Count >= 0 && Count <= this->Num());
1363 for (const ElementType* RESTRICT Start = GetData(), *RESTRICT Data = Start + Count; Data != Start; )
1364 {
1365 --Data;
1366 if (::Invoke(Pred, *Data))
1367 {
1368 return static_cast<SizeType>(Data - Start);
1369 }
1370 }
1371 return INDEX_NONE;
1372 }

1379 */
1380 template <typename Predicate>
1381 UE_NODEBUG [[nodiscard]] FORCEINLINE SizeType FindLastByPredicate(Predicate Pred) const
1382 {

1444 *

1496 /**
1497 * Filters the elements in the array based on a predicate functor.
1498 *
1499 * @param Pred The functor to apply to each element.
1500 * @returns TArray with the same type as this object which contains
1501 * the subset of elements for which the functor returns true.
1502 * @see FindByPredicate, ContainsByPredicate
1503 */
1504 template <typename Predicate>
1505 [[nodiscard]] TArray<ElementType> FilterByPredicate(Predicate Pred) const
1506 {
1507 TArray<ElementType> FilterResults;
1508 for (const ElementType* RESTRICT Data = GetData(), *RESTRICT DataEnd = Data + ArrayNum; Data != DataEnd; ++Data)
1509 {
1510 if (::Invoke(Pred, *Data))
1511 {
1512 FilterResults.Add(*Data);
1513 }
1514 }
1515 return FilterResults;
1516 }

1518 /**
1519 * Checks if this array contains the element.
1520 *
1521 * @returns True if found. False otherwise.
1522 * @see ContainsByPredicate, FilterByPredicate, FindByPredicate
1523 */
1524 template <typename ComparisonType>
1525 [[nodiscard]] bool Contains(const ComparisonType& Item) const
1526 {
1527 for (const ElementType* RESTRICT Data = GetData(), *RESTRICT DataEnd = Data + ArrayNum; Data != DataEnd; ++Data)
1528 {
1529 if (*Data == Item)
1530 {
1531 return true;
1532 }
1533 }
1534 return false;
1535 }

1541 * @returns True if found. False otherwise.

1543 */
1544 template <typename Predicate>

1576 /**
1577 * Bulk serialize array as a single memory blob when loading. Uses regular serialization code for saving
1578 * and doesn't serialize at all otherwise (e.g. transient, garbage collection, ...).
1579 *
1580 * Requirements:
1581 * - T's << operator needs to serialize ALL member variables in the SAME order they are layed out in memory.
1582 * - T's << operator can NOT perform any fixup operations. This limitation can be lifted by manually copying
1583 * the code after the BulkSerialize call.
1584 * - T can NOT contain any member variables requiring constructor calls or pointers
1585 * - sizeof(ElementType) must be equal to the sum of sizes of it's member variables.
1586 * - e.g. use pragma pack (push,1)/ (pop) to ensure alignment
1587 * - match up uint8/ WORDs so everything always end up being properly aligned
1588 * - Code can not rely on serialization of T if neither IsLoading() nor IsSaving() is true.
1589 * - Can only be called platforms that either have the same endianness as the one the content was saved with
1590 * or had the endian conversion occur in a cooking process like e.g. for consoles.
1591 *
1592 * Notes:
1593 * - it is safe to call BulkSerialize on TTransArrays
1594 *
1595 * IMPORTANT:
1596 * - This is Overridden in XeD3dResourceArray.h Please make certain changes are propagated accordingly
1597 *
1598 * @param Ar FArchive to bulk serialize this TArray to/from
1599 */
1600 void BulkSerialize(FArchive& Ar, bool bForcePerElementSerialization = false)
1601 {
1602 constexpr int32 ElementSize = sizeof(ElementType);
1603 // Serialize element size to detect mismatch across platforms.
1604 int32 SerializedElementSize = ElementSize;
1605 Ar << SerializedElementSize;
1606
1607 if (bForcePerElementSerialization
1608 || (Ar.IsSaving() // if we are saving, we always do the ordinary serialize as a way to make sure it matches up with bulk serialization
1609 && !Ar.IsCooking() // but cooking and transacting is performance critical, so we skip that
1610 && !Ar.IsTransacting())
1611 || Ar.IsByteSwapping() // if we are byteswapping, we need to do that per-element
1612 )
1613 {
1614 Ar << *this;
1615 }
1616 else
1617 {
1618 CountBytes(Ar);
1619 if (Ar.IsLoading())
1620 {
1621 // Basic sanity checking to ensure that sizes match.
1622 if (!ensure(SerializedElementSize == ElementSize))
1623 {
1624 Ar.SetError();
1625 return;
1626 }
1627
1628 // Serialize the number of elements, block allocate the right amount of memory and deserialize
1629 // the data as a giant memory blob in a single call to Serialize. Please see the function header
1630 // for detailed documentation on limitations and implications.
1631 SizeType NewArrayNum = 0;
1632 Ar << NewArrayNum;
1633 if (!ensure(NewArrayNum >= 0 && std::numeric_limits<SizeType>::max() / (SizeType)ElementSize >= NewArrayNum))
1634 {
1635 Ar.SetError();
1636 return;
1637 }
1638 Empty(NewArrayNum);
1639 AddUninitialized(NewArrayNum);
1640 Ar.Serialize(GetData(), (int64)NewArrayNum * (int64)ElementSize);
1641 }
1642 else if (Ar.IsSaving())
1643 {
1644 SizeType ArrayCount = Num();
1645 Ar << ArrayCount;
1646 Ar.Serialize(GetData(), (int64)ArrayCount * (int64)ElementSize);
1647 }
1648 }
1649 }
1650
1651 /**
1652 * Count bytes needed to serialize this array.
1653 *
1654 * @param Ar Archive to count for.
1655 */
1656 UE_NODEBUG void CountBytes(FArchive& Ar) const
1657 {
1658 Ar.CountBytes(ArrayNum*sizeof(ElementType), ArrayMax*sizeof(ElementType));
1659 }

1661 /**
1662 * Adds a given number of uninitialized elements into the array.
1663 *
1664 * Caution, AddUninitialized() will create elements without calling
1665 * the constructor and this is not appropriate for element types that
1666 * require a constructor to function properly.
1667 *
1668 * @param Count Number of elements to add.
1669 * @returns Number of elements in array before addition.
1670 */
1671 FORCEINLINE SizeType AddUninitialized()
1672 {
1673 // Begin sensitive code! Single element additions/insertions get inlined _everywhere_ and thus
1674 // punch above their weight with respect to exe size, so we pay a lot of attention to every instruction
1675 // here until we get in to the NOINLINE functions that actually handle the growth.
1676
1677 // Modulo some register allocation and pointer offsets, inlined sites on x64 for the "Tiny" path should look roughly like:
1678 //
1679 // mov eax, dword ptr [array + 8h] // load arraynum
1680 // cmp eax, dword ptr [array + 0Ch] // load arraymax
1681 // jne [to ArrayNum++]
1682 // mov ecx, immediate representing size/alignment
1683 // lea r8, [array + 0Ch]] // array max
1684 // lea rdx, [array] // allocator instance
1685 // call
1686 // lea ecx, [rax+1] // ArrayNum++
1687 // mov dword ptr [array + 8h], ecx // Save ArrayNum
1688 //
1689
1690 // Single cmp, which we can assume because we are adding a single element.
1691 if (ArrayNum == ArrayMax)
1692 {
1693 // Both branches here write the return in to ArrayNum. This is because the function call clobbers the registers
1694 // and if we assign as part of the return into something we need, the compiler doesn't have to reload the data
1695 // into the clobbered register.
1696
1697 // When we can pack size and alignment into a single 16 bit load, we save a parameter setup instruction
1698 // for the function call. The 16 bit part is load-bearing for arm codegen.
1699 // PVS believes this is overwrought because technically sizeof() <= 255 implies alignof <= 255. I think this is far more
1700 // clear and costs nothing.
1701 if constexpr (sizeof(ElementType) <= 255 && alignof(ElementType) <= 255) // -V590
1702 {
1703 // Note that the realloc functions are templated ONLY on allocator instance so they are not duplicated
1704 // in the code for every type!
1705 ArrayNum = UE::Core::Private::ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc_Tiny<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(sizeof(ElementType) | (alignof(ElementType) << 8), AllocatorInstance, ArrayMax);
1706 }
1707 else
1708 {
1709 ArrayNum = UE::Core::Private::ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(sizeof(ElementType), alignof(ElementType), AllocatorInstance, ArrayMax);
1710 }
1711 }
1712 // End sensitive code!
1713
1714 SizeType OldArrayNum = ArrayNum;
1715 ArrayNum++;
1716 return OldArrayNum;
1717 }
1718 FORCEINLINE SizeType AddUninitialized(SizeType Count)
1719 {
1720 // Should be SetNumUninitialized?
1721 return UE::Core::Private::ReallocGrow<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(
1722 sizeof(ElementType),
1723 alignof(ElementType),
1724 Count,
1725 AllocatorInstance,
1726 ArrayNum,
1727 ArrayMax
1728 );
1729 }
1730
1731private:
1732 void InsertUninitializedImpl(SizeType Index)
1733 {
1734 // Begin sensitive code! See comments in AddUninitialized() before touching!
1735 if (ArrayNum == ArrayMax)
1736 {
1737 if constexpr (sizeof(ElementType) <= 255 && alignof(ElementType) <= 255) // -V590
1738 {
1739 ArrayNum = UE::Core::Private::ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc_Tiny<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(sizeof(ElementType) | (alignof(ElementType) << 8), AllocatorInstance, ArrayMax);
1740 }
1741 else
1742 {
1743 ArrayNum = UE::Core::Private::ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(sizeof(ElementType), alignof(ElementType), AllocatorInstance, ArrayMax);
1744 }
1745 }
1746 // End sensitive code!
1747 SizeType OldNum = ArrayNum;
1748 ArrayNum++;
1749 ElementType* Data = GetData() + Index;
1750 RelocateConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)(Data + 1), Data, OldNum - Index);
1751 }
1752 void InsertUninitializedImpl(SizeType Index, SizeType Count)
1753 {
1754 // Should be SetNumUninitialized?
1755 SizeType OldNum = UE::Core::Private::ReallocGrow<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(
1756 sizeof(ElementType),
1757 alignof(ElementType),
1758 Count,
1759 AllocatorInstance,
1760 ArrayNum,
1761 ArrayMax
1762 );
1763 ElementType* Data = GetData() + Index;
1764 RelocateConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)(Data + Count), Data, OldNum - Index);
1765 }
1766 template <
1767 typename OtherSizeType
1768 UE_REQUIRES(sizeof(OtherSizeType) > sizeof(SizeType))
1769 >
1770 UE_NODEBUG void InsertUninitializedImpl(SizeType Index, OtherSizeType Count)
1771 {
1772 checkf((OtherSizeType)(SizeType)Count == Count, TEXT("Invalid number of elements to add to this array type: %lld"), (long long)(SizeType)Count);
1773 return InsertUninitializedImpl(Index, (SizeType)Count);
1774 }

2048 void RemoveAtImpl(SizeType Index)
2049 {
2050 ElementType* Dest = GetData() + Index;
2051
2052 DestructItem(Dest);
2053
2054 // Skip relocation in the common case that there is nothing to move.
2055 SizeType NumToMove = (ArrayNum - Index) - 1;
2056 if (NumToMove)
2057 {
2058 RelocateConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)Dest, Dest + 1, NumToMove);
2059 }
2060 --ArrayNum;
2061
2062 SlackTrackerNumChanged();
2063 }

2065 void RemoveAtImpl(SizeType Index, SizeType Count)
2066 {
2067 ElementType* Dest = GetData() + Index;
2068
2069 DestructItems(Dest, Count);
2070
2071 // Skip relocation in the common case that there is nothing to move.
2072 SizeType NumToMove = (ArrayNum - Index) - Count;
2073 if (NumToMove)
2074 {
2075 RelocateConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)Dest, Dest + Count, NumToMove);
2076 }
2077 ArrayNum -= Count;
2078
2079 SlackTrackerNumChanged();
2080 }

2144private:
2145 void RemoveAtSwapImpl(SizeType Index)
2146 {
2147 ElementType* Data = GetData();
2148 ElementType* Dest = Data + Index;
2149
2150 DestructItem(Dest);
2151
2152 // Replace the elements in the hole created by the removal with elements from the end of the array, so the range of indices used by the array is contiguous.
2153 const SizeType NumElementsAfterHole = (ArrayNum - Index) - 1;
2154 const SizeType NumElementsToMoveIntoHole = FPlatformMath::Min(1, NumElementsAfterHole);
2155 if (NumElementsToMoveIntoHole)
2156 {
2157 RelocateConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)Dest, Data + (ArrayNum - NumElementsToMoveIntoHole), NumElementsToMoveIntoHole);
2158 }
2159 --ArrayNum;
2160
2161 SlackTrackerNumChanged();
2162 }
2163
2164 void RemoveAtSwapImpl(SizeType Index, SizeType Count)
2165 {
2166 ElementType* Data = GetData();
2167 ElementType* Dest = Data + Index;
2168
2169 DestructItems(Dest, Count);
2170
2171 // Replace the elements in the hole created by the removal with elements from the end of the array, so the range of indices used by the array is contiguous.
2172 const SizeType NumElementsAfterHole = (ArrayNum - Index) - Count;
2173 const SizeType NumElementsToMoveIntoHole = FPlatformMath::Min(Count, NumElementsAfterHole);
2174 if (NumElementsToMoveIntoHole)
2175 {
2176 RelocateConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)Dest, Data + (ArrayNum - NumElementsToMoveIntoHole), NumElementsToMoveIntoHole);
2177 }
2178 ArrayNum -= Count;
2179
2180 SlackTrackerNumChanged();
2181 }

2253 /**
2254 * Same as empty, but doesn't change memory allocations, unless the new size is larger than
2255 * the current array. It calls the destructors on held items if needed and then zeros the ArrayNum.
2256 *
2257 * @param NewSize The expected usage size after calling this function.
2258 */

2260 {
2261 if (NewSize < 0)
2262 {
2263 // Cast to USizeType first to prevent sign extension on negative sizes, producing unusually large values.
2264 UE::Core::Private::OnInvalidArrayNum((unsigned long long)(USizeType)NewSize);

2268 if (NewSize <= ArrayMax)
2269 {
2270 DestructItems(GetData(), ArrayNum);
2271 ArrayNum = 0;
2272
2273 SlackTrackerNumChanged();
2274 }
2275 else
2276 {
2277 Empty(NewSize);
2278 }

2413 /**
2414 * Appends the specified array to this array.
2415 *
2416 * AllocatorType changing version.
2417 *
2418 * @param Source The array to append.
2419 * @see Add, Insert
2420 */
2421 template <typename OtherElementType, typename OtherAllocatorType>
2422 void Append(const TArray<OtherElementType, OtherAllocatorType>& Source)
2423 {
2424 check((void*)this != (void*)&Source);
2425
2426 SizeType SourceCount = Source.Num();
2427
2428 // Do nothing if the source is empty.
2429 if (!SourceCount)
2430 {
2431 return;
2432 }
2433
2434 // Allocate memory for the new elements.
2435 SizeType Pos = AddUninitialized(SourceCount);
2436 ConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)(GetData() + Pos), Source.GetData(), SourceCount);
2437 }

2564 /**
2565 * Constructs a new item at the end of the array, possibly reallocating the whole array to fit.
2566 *
2567 * @param Args The arguments to forward to the constructor of the new item.
2568 * @return Index to the new item
2569 */
2570 template <typename... ArgsType>
2571 FORCEINLINE SizeType Emplace(ArgsType&&... Args)
2572 {
2573 // If this fails to compile when trying to call Emplace with a non-public constructor,
2574 // do not make TArray a friend.
2575 //
2576 // Instead, prefer this pattern:
2577 //
2578 // class FMyType
2579 // {
2580 // private:
2581 // struct FPrivateToken { explicit FPrivateToken() = default; };
2582 //
2583 // public:
2584 // // This has an equivalent access level to a private constructor,
2585 // // as only friends of FMyType will have access to FPrivateToken,
2586 // // but Emplace can legally call it since it's public.
2587 // explicit FMyType(FPrivateToken, int32 Int, float Real, const TCHAR* String);
2588 // };
2589 //
2590 // TArray<FMyType> Arr:
2591 //
2592 // // Won't compile if the caller doesn't have access to FMyType::FPrivateToken
2593 // Arr.Emplace(FMyType::FPrivateToken{}, 5, 3.14f, TEXT("Banana"));
2594 //
2595
2596 // Begin sensitive code! See comments in AddUninitialized() before touching!
2597 if (ArrayNum == ArrayMax)
2598 {
2599 if constexpr (sizeof(ElementType) <= 255 && alignof(ElementType) <= 255) // -V590
2600 {
2601 ArrayNum = UE::Core::Private::ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc_Tiny<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(sizeof(ElementType) | (alignof(ElementType) << 8), AllocatorInstance, ArrayMax);
2602 }
2603 else
2604 {
2605 ArrayNum = UE::Core::Private::ReallocGrow1_DoAlloc<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(sizeof(ElementType), alignof(ElementType), AllocatorInstance, ArrayMax);
2606 }
2607 }
2608 // End sensitive code!
2609 SizeType OldArrayNum = ArrayNum;
2610 ArrayNum++;
2611 void* Ptr = (char*)AllocatorInstance.GetAllocation() + sizeof(ElementType) * OldArrayNum;
2612 (void)new (Ptr) ElementType(Forward<ArgsType>(Args)...);
2613 return OldArrayNum;
2614 }

3064 * maintaining order but not indices.
3065 *
3066 * @param Item The item to remove.
3067 * @returns The number of items removed. For RemoveSingleItem, this is always either 0 or 1.
3068 * @see Add, Insert, Remove, RemoveAll, RemoveAllSwap
3069 */

3071 {

3073 if (Index == INDEX_NONE)

3079

3101 SizeType Remove(const ElementType& Item)

3109 /**
3110 * Remove all instances that match the predicate, maintaining order but not indices
3111 * Optimized to work with runs of matches/non-matches
3112 *
3113 * @param Predicate Predicate class instance
3114 * @returns Number of removed elements.
3115 * @see Add, Insert, RemoveAllSwap, RemoveSingle, RemoveSwap
3116 */
3117 template <class PREDICATE_CLASS>
3118 SizeType RemoveAll(const PREDICATE_CLASS& Predicate)
3119 {
3120 const SizeType OriginalNum = ArrayNum;
3121 if (!OriginalNum)
3122 {
3123 return 0; // nothing to do, loop assumes one item so need to deal with this edge case here
3124 }
3125
3126 ElementType* Data = GetData();
3127
3128 SizeType WriteIndex = 0;
3129 SizeType ReadIndex = 0;
3130 bool bNotMatch = !::Invoke(Predicate, Data[ReadIndex]); // use a ! to guarantee it can't be anything other than zero or one
3131 do
3132 {
3133 SizeType RunStartIndex = ReadIndex++;
3134 while (ReadIndex < OriginalNum && bNotMatch == !::Invoke(Predicate, Data[ReadIndex]))
3135 {
3136 ReadIndex++;
3137 }
3138 SizeType RunLength = ReadIndex - RunStartIndex;
3139 checkSlow(RunLength > 0);
3140 if (bNotMatch)
3141 {
3142 // this was a non-matching run, we need to move it
3143 if (WriteIndex != RunStartIndex)
3144 {
3145 RelocateConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)(Data + WriteIndex), Data + RunStartIndex, RunLength);
3146 }
3147 WriteIndex += RunLength;
3148 }
3149 else
3150 {
3151 // this was a matching run, delete it
3152 DestructItems(Data + RunStartIndex, RunLength);
3153 }
3154 bNotMatch = !bNotMatch;
3155 } while (ReadIndex < OriginalNum);
3156
3157 ArrayNum = WriteIndex;
3158
3159 SlackTrackerNumChanged();
3160
3161 return OriginalNum - ArrayNum;
3162 }

3164 /**
3165 * Remove all instances that match the predicate
3166 *
3167 * @param Predicate Predicate class instance
3168 * @param AllowShrinking Tell if this function can shrink the memory in-use if suitable.
3169 * @see Remove, RemoveSingle, RemoveSingleSwap, RemoveSwap
3170 */
3171 template <class PREDICATE_CLASS>
3172 SizeType RemoveAllSwap(const PREDICATE_CLASS& Predicate, EAllowShrinking AllowShrinking = EAllowShrinking::Default)
3173 {
3174 bool bRemoved = false;
3175 const SizeType OriginalNum = ArrayNum;
3176 for (SizeType ItemIndex = 0; ItemIndex < Num();)
3177 {
3178 if (::Invoke(Predicate, (*this)[ItemIndex]))
3179 {
3180 bRemoved = true;
3181 RemoveAtSwap(ItemIndex, EAllowShrinking::No);
3182 }
3183 else
3184 {
3185 ++ItemIndex;
3186 }
3187 }
3188
3189 if (bRemoved && AllowShrinking == EAllowShrinking::Yes)
3190 {
3191 UE::Core::Private::ReallocShrink<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(
3192 sizeof(ElementType),
3193 alignof(ElementType),
3194 AllocatorInstance,
3195 ArrayNum,
3196 ArrayMax
3197 );
3198 }
3199
3200 return OriginalNum - ArrayNum;
3201 }

3205 {
3206 return RemoveAllSwap(Predicate, bAllowShrinking ? EAllowShrinking::Yes : EAllowShrinking::No);

3256 bool bRemoved = false;

3258 {
3259 if ((*this)[Index] == Item)
3260 {
3261 bRemoved = true;
3262 RemoveAtSwap(Index--, EAllowShrinking::No);

3269 sizeof(ElementType),

3317 /**
3318 * Searches for the first entry of the specified type, will only work with
3319 * TArray<UObject*>. Optionally return the item's index, and can specify
3320 * the start index.
3321 *
3322 * @param Item (Optional output) If it's not null, then it will point to
3323 * the found element. Untouched if element hasn't been found.
3324 * @param ItemIndex (Optional output) If it's not null, then it will be set
3325 * to the position of found element in the array. Untouched if
3326 * element hasn't been found.
3327 * @param StartIndex (Optional) Index in array at which the function should
3328 * start to look for element.
3329 * @returns True if element was found. False otherwise.
3330 */
3331 template<typename SearchType>
3332 bool FindItemByClass(SearchType **Item = nullptr, SizeType *ItemIndex = nullptr, SizeType StartIndex = 0) const
3333 {
3334 UClass* SearchClass = SearchType::StaticClass();
3335 for (SizeType Idx = StartIndex; Idx < ArrayNum; Idx++)
3336 {
3337 if ((*this)[Idx] != nullptr && (*this)[Idx]->IsA(SearchClass))
3338 {
3339 if (Item != nullptr)
3340 {
3341 *Item = (SearchType*)((*this)[Idx]);
3342 }
3343 if (ItemIndex != nullptr)
3344 {
3345 *ItemIndex = Idx;
3346 }
3347 return true;
3348 }
3349 }
3350 return false;
3351 }

3496 /**
3497 * Copies data from one array into this array. Uses the fast path if the
3498 * data in question does not need a constructor.
3499 *
3500 * @param Source The source array to copy
3501 * @param PrevMax The previous allocated size
3502 */
3503 template <typename OtherElementType, typename OtherSizeType>
3504 void CopyToEmpty(const OtherElementType* OtherData, OtherSizeType OtherNum, SizeType PrevMax)
3505 {
3506 SizeType NewNum = (SizeType)OtherNum;
3507 checkf((OtherSizeType)NewNum == OtherNum, TEXT("Invalid number of elements to add to this array type: %lld"), (long long)NewNum);
3508
3509 ArrayNum = NewNum;
3510 if (OtherNum || PrevMax)
3511 {
3512 UE::Core::Private::ReallocForCopy<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(
3513 sizeof(ElementType),
3514 alignof(ElementType),
3515 NewNum,
3516 PrevMax,
3517 AllocatorInstance,
3518 ArrayNum,
3519 ArrayMax
3520 );
3521 ConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)GetData(), OtherData, OtherNum);
3522 }
3523 else
3524 {
3525 ArrayMax = AllocatorInstance.GetInitialCapacity();
3526 }
3527
3528 SlackTrackerNumChanged();
3529 }

3531 /**
3532 * Copies data from one array into this array. Uses the fast path if the
3533 * data in question does not need a constructor.
3534 *
3535 * @param Source The source array to copy
3536 * @param PrevMax The previous allocated size
3537 * @param ExtraSlack Additional amount of memory to allocate at
3538 * the end of the buffer. Counted in elements.
3539 */
3540 template <typename OtherElementType, typename OtherSizeType>
3541 void CopyToEmptyWithSlack(const OtherElementType* OtherData, OtherSizeType OtherNum, SizeType PrevMax, SizeType ExtraSlack)
3542 {
3543 SizeType NewNum = (SizeType)OtherNum;
3544 checkf((OtherSizeType)NewNum == OtherNum, TEXT("Invalid number of elements to add to this array type: %lld"), (long long)NewNum);
3545
3546 ArrayNum = NewNum;
3547 if (OtherNum || ExtraSlack || PrevMax)
3548 {
3549 USizeType NewMax = NewNum + ExtraSlack;
3550
3551 // This should only happen when we've underflowed or overflowed SizeType
3552 if ((SizeType)NewMax < NewNum)
3553 {
3554 UE::Core::Private::OnInvalidArrayNum((unsigned long long)NewMax);
3555 }
3556
3557 UE::Core::Private::ReallocForCopy<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(
3558 sizeof(ElementType),
3559 alignof(ElementType),
3560 NewNum + ExtraSlack,
3561 PrevMax,
3562 AllocatorInstance,
3563 ArrayNum,
3564 ArrayMax
3565 );
3566 ConstructItems<ElementType>((void*)GetData(), OtherData, OtherNum);
3567 }
3568 else
3569 {
3570 ArrayMax = AllocatorInstance.GetInitialCapacity();
3571 }
3572
3573 SlackTrackerNumChanged();
3574 }

4042struct TArrayPrivateFriend
4043{
4044 /**
4045 * Serialization operator.
4046 *
4047 * @param Ar Archive to serialize the array with.
4048 * @param A Array to serialize.
4049 * @returns Passing the given archive.
4050 */
4051 template<typename ElementType, typename AllocatorType>
4052 static FArchive& Serialize(FArchive& Ar, TArray<ElementType, AllocatorType>& A)
4053 {
4054 A.CountBytes(Ar);
4055
4056 // For net archives, limit serialization to 16MB, to protect against excessive allocation
4057 using SizeType = typename AllocatorType::SizeType;
4058 constexpr SizeType MaxNetArraySerialize = (16 * 1024 * 1024) / sizeof(ElementType);
4059 SizeType SerializeNum = Ar.IsLoading() ? 0 : A.ArrayNum;
4060
4061 Ar << SerializeNum;
4062
4063 if (SerializeNum == 0)
4064 {
4065 // if we are loading, then we have to reset the size to 0, in case it isn't currently 0
4066 if (Ar.IsLoading())
4067 {
4068 A.Empty();
4069 }
4070 return Ar;
4071 }
4072
4073 if (Ar.IsError() || SerializeNum < 0 || !ensure(!Ar.IsNetArchive() || SerializeNum <= MaxNetArraySerialize))
4074 {
4075 Ar.SetError();
4076 return Ar;
4077 }
4078
4079 // if we don't need to perform per-item serialization, just read it in bulk
4080 if constexpr (sizeof(ElementType) == 1 || TCanBulkSerialize<ElementType>::Value)
4081 {
4082 A.ArrayNum = SerializeNum;
4083
4084 // Serialize simple bytes which require no construction or destruction.
4085 if ((A.ArrayNum || A.ArrayMax) && Ar.IsLoading())
4086 {
4087 UE::Core::Private::ReallocForCopy<UE::Core::Private::GetAllocatorFlags<AllocatorType>()>(
4088 sizeof(ElementType),
4089 alignof(ElementType),
4090 A.ArrayNum,
4091 A.ArrayMax,
4092 A.AllocatorInstance,
4093 A.ArrayNum,
4094 A.ArrayMax
4095 );
4096 }
4097
4098 if constexpr (TIsUECoreVariant<ElementType, double>::Value)
4099 {
4100 if (Ar.IsLoading() && Ar.UEVer() < EUnrealEngineObjectUE5Version::LARGE_WORLD_COORDINATES)
4101 {
4102 // Per item serialization is required for core variant types loaded from pre LWC archives, to enable conversion from float to double.
4103 A.Empty(SerializeNum);
4104 for (SizeType i = 0; i < SerializeNum; i++)
4105 {
4106 Ar << A.AddDefaulted_GetRef();
4107 }
4108 }
4109 else

4111 Ar.Serialize(A.GetData(), A.Num() * sizeof(ElementType));
4112 }
4113 }
4114 else

4116 Ar.Serialize(A.GetData(), A.Num() * sizeof(ElementType));
4117 }
4118
4119 }
4120 else if (Ar.IsLoading())
4121 {
4122 // Required for resetting ArrayNum
4123 A.Empty(SerializeNum);
4124
4125 for (SizeType i=0; i<SerializeNum; i++)
4126 {
4127 Ar << A.AddDefaulted_GetRef();
4128 }
4129 }
4130 else

4133

4135 {
4136 Ar << A[i];
4137 }
4138 }
4139
4140 A.SlackTrackerNumChanged();
4141
4142 return Ar;
4143 }
